cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper is about age estimation from facial images using deep learning methods. The main focus is on developing two Deep Differentiable Random Forests methods for this task. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper involves joint learning of input-dependent data partitions and age distributions, which suggests that it may also belong to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and the inhomogeneous nature of facial feature space w.r.t. ages further supports the possibility of cs.MM (multimedia) and cs.IR (information retrieval) sub-categories.
